sourceMeaningMnemonic: The <radical>feather</radical> radical and <kanji>feather</kanji> are the same in looks as well as in meaning.
meaningInfo: Have you been studying your radicals? If so, this'll be easy!
readingMnemonic: All these <kanji>feather</kanji>s. You're a bird man / woman, and you're getting ready to fly. Just as you're about to take off, someone dumps you with <reading>honey</reading> <ja>はね</ja> and you're all goopy, unable to go anywhere.
readingInfo: Taste the honey, feel it all over your feathers. Go ahead and plummet towards the ground (because you were jumping off a building to fly when someone doused you with honey). At least it's a tasty way to go, no?
